//! Supremus-style GPU preflop auxiliary CFVNet training pipeline.
//!
//! Fundamentally different from the river/turn/flop pipelines -- NO CFR solving.
//! Instead, each training sample is generated by:
//!
//! 1. Sampling a random preflop situation (ranges + pot + stack, no board)
//! 2. Enumerating the 1,755 canonical flops (suit-isomorphic representatives
//!    with combinatorial weights, instead of all C(52,3) = 22,100)
//! 3. Running a batched forward pass through the trained flop model
//! 4. Weighted-averaging the flop model outputs across canonical flops per combo
//! 5. Inserting the averaged CFVs as training targets
//!
//! The preflop model learns to predict the weighted-average flop model output
//! from just ranges + pot + stack (no board information). Its input uses the
//! same 2720-dim format but with board one-hot and rank presence set to all zeros.
//!
//! Pipeline: sample preflop situations -> encode canonical flops -> flop model
//!           inference -> weighted average across flops -> reservoir insert -> train

